Heat oil in stockpot on medium-high heat. Add sausage to pan; saute 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Add onion; saute 3 minutes. Add salt and garlic; saute 1 minute. Add leek and apple; saute 8 minutes. Add chicken; saute 4 minutes, browning on all sides. Stir in broth and water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.